@maximumsellerusÂ  Â You stated the buyer opened a return through eBay.Â  No matter what the message may have said make SURE you go into the return request and accept the return and select the option for eBay to supply a label.Â  YOU MUST DO THIS or in a few days eBay will AUTOMATICALLY refund the buyer from your account.Â  Â If the buyer closes the return then you are ok, but until that happens, accept the return to protect yourself.Â By the way, on eBay it's not really a great idea to offer a partial refund.Â  There are buyers that will take advantage of seller's that are willing to offer a partial if they complain.Â  The correct answer is almost always: "Sorry you are unhappy with your purchase, please return for a full refund"

